open Set Topology

then either f(z) ‚â° c or else z0 is a zero of f - c of order m and there exists a neighborhood V of z0
such that f‚Åª¬π' {c} ‚à© V consists of exactly m points (with multiplicity).

This statement is translated using differentiability (holomorphic) and a local factorization form: either
f is constant c on U or there exists m ‚â• 1 and a holomorphic g with g(z0) ‚â† 0 and an open neighborhood V
on which f(z) - c = (z - z0)^m * g(z).

theorem jirilebl_zero_multiplicity_or_constant {U : Set ‚ÑÇ} {f : ‚ÑÇ ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ} (hU : IsOpen U) (hf : DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ f U)
  {z0 c : ‚ÑÇ} (hz0 : z0 ‚àà U) (hfc : f z0 = c) :

    ‚àÄ z ‚àà V, f z - c = (z - z0) ^ m * g z) := by sorry
